    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsing LSP hover, I used this API expecting `boolean` to be returned, but it returns `0` or `1`.\n\nFrom `vimfn.gen.lua` documentation for `vim.fn.filereadable`:\n\n```lua\n--- Returns |TRUE| if {file} exists, can be read, and is not\n--- a directory, else |FALSE|.\n---\n--- {file} is any expression, which is used as a String. If you\n--- don't care about the file being readable you can use |glob()|.\n---\n--- {file} is used as-is, you may want to expand wildcards first: >vim\n---   echo filereadable('~/.vimrc')\n--- < >\n---   0\n--- < >vim\n---   echo filereadable(expand('~/.vimrc'))\n--- < >\n---   1\n--- <\n---\n--- @param file string\n--- @return 0|1\nfunction vim.fn.filereadable(file) end\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nif vim.fn.filereadable(vim.fn.expand('somefile')) then\n  -- 0 and 1 are truthy, so this block will always run.\nend\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither \n- Update docs to say it returns 0|1\n- Update the function to return true|false as doc states\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nCachyOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.27.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\ncachyos-extra-v3 (based on arch package repo)",
